The dining room. In this room you are met with rows and rows of tables and benches for meals. Directly in front of you at the back of the room is where you can collect your food in a rectangular window area you'd see in school lunch halls. Meals are provided for you depeding on what time of the day it is. Oddly, you can never find the person who makes this food. The food is either really abysmal in larger servings, or at it's finest in tiny quantities. (OOC note: I'll try keep up with this for you, but it'll follow previous British meal times. This is breakfast in the morning, dinner being the main meal at around midday and tea being in the early evening) If you don't find the food provided provided appealing, then you can go make your own food in the #kitchens which you enter through a door to the left of the window area. If you don't like doors, you can just hop through the window space to get into it. To the right of window gap, you will find trays to put plates on as well as any piece of cutlery, condiment or such you require for all mealtimes of the day. You also oddly don't see the person who cleans these as they replenish daily (edited)
